9:
Those three are out shopping. I
wanted to help carry things, but I
decided against it.
11:
I feared I might blow the roofs off of
houses again.
15:
Oh yeah... I did have a lot of hope for
Greatwyrm Delivery Services at first...
19:
It is strange. I thought nothing would
change in me ever again... And yet I
chose to work and fight once more.
21:
Perhaps Mertina and the others are
changing, as well...
26:
Do you not want to be with them
anymore, Schult?
30: That... That is not the case...
34:
So you want to be together with
them?
40:
Those three... They gave me a desire
to understand humans.
43: ...But now... I want to know them.
45:
What is it they want? What, as
humans, would make them happy...
48:
Don't overthink this, Mertina. We can
take our time to think this over.
49:
But your mind has been made up
from the beginning, hasn't it, Lucia?
You don't intend to change it, do you?
60:
Carlo, that man! He came and took
her to the village!
65:
Is this perhaps... what Mertina
wishes for?
68:
Lord Schult. You often speak of
wanting to understand humans.
70:
...Then let us tell you more about
ourselves.
73:
C-Carlo, wait! You don't need to pull
so hard—
75:
We're going to go back to the village
and talk to everyone, okay? It'll be
fine! I'll make sure you can go back
to your old life—
77: Tch... D-don't worry! This time, I-I'll...
79:
...His wings. I feel safe and warm
when I sleep under them.
81:
He worked hard to understand me.
He stayed with me, always. His
kindness brought me joy I've never
known!
83:
I want him to be there for me, not
you!
93:
W-wait! The village won't stand for
that!
99:
However... following the whims of
others and finding happiness...
Those things are far from similar.
These three taught me that.
102:
...Thank you. I'm glad you
remembered me after all this time.
104:
Now go find another girl to save,
okay?
112:
Earlier... I heard your scream. But it
didn't sound like it was for me.
115:
...B-but... What I just said... That's how
I truly feel!
116:
Lord Schult... Your kindness... Your
warmth... I—
118:
...Being able to sit down and dine
with you, Lord Schult... It's a joy
unmatched.
119:
And I've been thinking about this for
some time, but your face when your
mouth is full... It's the cutest, most
wonderful thing to see!
121:
...I like your sturdy and powerful
back, Lord Schult. You're as
dependable as they come.
122:
You accepted us for who we are.
Nobody could ever be more
wonderful than you...
124:
...You are our happiness, Lord Schult.
We choose to be with you.
129:
...I see. So, that's how you were
feeling.
134:
Then allow me to give my answer,
too.
137:
In times of illness... and in times of
health.
140:
In times of suffering, and in times of
joy... Till death do us part. 
Lucia. Aileen. Mertina.
143: I promise to be with you, always.
146:
...Let us dine and rest together once
more.
148:
Stay by my side, and tell me more
about who you are.
155:
The stars tonight... They are... more
beautiful than I could have
imagined.
161: You all look like you had fun.
164:
Indeed. It seems they enjoyed
themselves. With this saddle, there is
no fear of falling, either.
167:
You three will ride not in a
horse-drawn carriage... Your
personal steed will instead be a
dragon. I will take you anywhere,
anytime.
175:
Oh, don't mind me! I was just
thinking out loud—
178:
He's even more dependent on them
than he was before. Right?
